suncertify.presentation
Interface BookingModel

All Known Implementing Classes:
BookingModelImp, BookingModelNwImp
public interface BookingModel

This interface is to be implemented by the model class used in the model viewer controller design pattern for the presentation tier of the Booking application. It contains several methods that must be implemented so that it can represent and manipulate the data contained in the database by interacting with the business tier of the application.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Robert Black

searchContractors

java.util.Map<java.lang.Long,Contractor> searchContractors(java.lang.String name,
                                                           java.lang.String location)
                                                           throws RecordNotFoundException
A method that handles a call from the BookingController that will call the BookingBusinessAdapter to search for records according to entered criteria ("name" and / or "location". A no entry value matches any field value. An entry will match any field value that begins with criteria entered e.g. "Fred" matches "Fred" or "Freddy" Records are returned as a HashMap containing a Long as the key which represents the record number (file position) and a Contractor object as the value which represents the record its self.

Parameters:
name - the name search criteria.
location - the location search criteria.
Returns:
a HashMap of records numbers and Contractor objects.
Throws:
RecordNotFoundException - if the record is deleted or doesn't exist.
SecurityException - if the record is locked with a cookie other than lockCookie.

bookContractor

void bookContractor(long recNo,
                    java.lang.String custNo)
                    throws RecordNotFoundException,
                           SecurityException,
                           RecordAlreadyBookedException
A method that handles a call from the BookingController that will call the BookingBusinessAdapter to book the contractor record in question.

Parameters:
recNo - the record number (file position).
custNo - the eight digit customer id.
Throws:
RecordNotFoundException - if the record is deleted or doesn't exist.
SecurityException - if the record is locked with a cookie other than lockCookie.
RecordAlreadyBookedException - if the record already has a customer number
